  "texts": [
    "Several mechanisms to quality assure user feedback were proposed, including:• Quantifying the discrepancy in the quality of user feedback [45].",
    "• Focusing on fairness criteria that users found important, including affordability, equality of opportunity, and individual fairness [43].",
    "• Including feedback from non-WEIRD (Western, Educated, Industrialised, Rich, Democratic) users [43].",
    "• Approaching the selection of the user population thoughtfully [43].",
    "This was because perceived fairness was likely to vary across geographic locations and local cultures.• Conducting continuous evaluation of fairness, especially to adapt to changing stakeholder expectations and dynamic real-world conditions [42,46]."
